budget-conscious and those visitors wishing to experience authentic indonesian (but not balinese) cuisine. these are usually marked with a prominent masakan padang sign and serve food from padang, sumatra. the options are usually stacked on plates in the window, you choose what you want and it is served with steamed rice. the most famous padang speciality is rendang sapi (spicy beef coconut curry) but there are always a number of chicken, fish, egg and vegetable options. padang food is always halal and you will eat well for rp 15,000-20,000. balinese food[edit] actual balinese food is common on the island but 